org.nerd4j.csv.parser

Interface CSVParser

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable, Closeable

    public interface CSVParser
extends Closeable
    Reads character data from a Reader, parsing and tokenizing them into CSVToken.

    After usage it should be closed to permit resource release.

    Synchronization

    CSV parsers are not synchronized. It is recommended to create separate CSV parser instances for each thread. If multiple threads access a CSV parser concurrently, it must be synchronized externally.

    Author:
    Nerd4j Team

      • skip

        CSVToken skip()
       throws IOException
        Read the next CSVToken and returns it. The result CSVToken will be returned from getCurrentToken() too.

        The method getCurrentValue() won't return any value.

        Returns:
        next read CSVToken.
        Throws:
